author: Written by: Sam Winstrom, Assignment Editor
title: Woman carjacked in Mid City early Saturday morning
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - Two unknown men carjacked a woman in Mid City Saturday morning.
According to NOPD, the 34-year-old woman was sitting in her vehicle in the 4000 block of Tulane Avenue around 3 a.m. when an unknown black male approached her and asked to use her cellphone. Another unknown man armed with a gun approached her and said "this is a carjacking get out of the vehicle," according to NOPD.
The woman complied and the two men fled in her vehicle.
Anyone with information on this incident is asked to call CRIMESTOPPERS at 504-822-1111.
